title: 820-3208 No turning on, fan spins 1 seg every 5 seg.
message:
Hi, i have a macbook air 820-3208 here.

measures: 

PPBUS_G3H @ R6920 8,37v (8,34v when fan spins thats one seg)
PPVIN_SW_TBTBST @ C3891 0,94v to 1,90v fluctuating every seg
PPBUS_S5_HS_COMPUTING_ISNS @ C7516 8,37v (8,36-8,35 when fan spins)
PPBUS_S5_HS_OTHER_ISNS @ C7200 8,37v (8,35v when spins)
PPDCIN_G3H_ISOL @ R6905 16,93v (16,88v when spins)
PP3V42_G3H @ R5077 3,42v stable
PPVRTC_G3H @ R1801 3.33v stable
PP5V_S5 @ L5720 5,01v (5,12 when spins)
PP5V_SUS @ C7840 5,05v stable
PP3V3_S5 @ C9480 3,33v stable
SMC_RESET_L @ R5000 3,38v stable

green light and orange light but no turning on, no spin continuosly.

title: 820-3208 No turning on, fan spins 1 seg every 5 seg.
820-3208 No turning on, fan spins 1 seg every 5 seg.
message:
We do sleep from time to time!

Where was the liquid? 

No pulsing on CPU vcore is no good. 

What does U2700 area look like? How high does SYSCLK_CLK32K_RTC voltage spike? What's the resistance between pins 17/18 on U7000? Do you have any short circuits to ground on PP3V3_S0 and other S0 rails? 

On everything before 2013 most common quarter fan spin causes are clock and battery-side current sensing on the ISL6259, but usually that does come with CPU vcore - so I'll be waiting for you to tell me where the corrosion was so we can go further.

The SYSCLK_CLK32K_RTC At pin 12 of the U2700 have 0.43v stable.. The resistance between pin 17/18 on U7000 is 03.0 ohms .. On PPVCORE_S0_CPU have 03,3 ohms.. :(
